{
  "text": "When comparing the results from this study to previous studies, several aspects are important to bear in mind. Given the lack of a common definition of medical complications, as well as different methods of data collection, different studies are difficult to correctly compare. For example, in the Twin Cities Marathon study, all injuries and collapses were registered, whilst in this study, only runners suffering from severe collapse and in need of advanced medical care were included. Thereby, it is unsurprising that incidence rates were higher in Roberts study [CITATION_1] .",
